  "prompt": "How has legislation evolved to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Legislation combating money laundering has evolved significantly over time:\n\n1. Early Stages\n- Bank Secrecy Act (1970) in the US\n- Initial focus on reporting large cash transactions\n- Limited international cooperation\n\n2. International Developments\n- FATF (Financial Action Task Force) established in 1989\n- Created global anti-money laundering standards\n- Developed recommendations for financial institutions\n\n3. Key Legislative Milestones\n- Money Laundering Control Act (1986)\n- USA PATRIOT Act (2001)\n- Enhanced reporting requirements\n- Increased penalties for financial crimes\n- Expanded definition of money laundering\n\n4. Modern Regulatory Approaches\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Enhanced due diligence requirements\n- Risk-based compliance frameworks\n- Advanced technology for transaction monitoring\n\n5. Cryptocurrency Regulations\n- Growing focus on digital currency transactions\n- Implementation of blockchain tracking mechanisms\n- Developing comprehensive regulatory frameworks\n\n6. Recent Trends\n- Increased international collaboration\n- Stricter compliance requirements\n- Sophisticated technological surveillance\n- Broader scope of financial investigations\n\nThe legislation continues to adapt to emerging financial technologies and complex global financial networks.",
